The paper also discusses the use of soft gating mechanisms, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and falls under the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for NLP tasks, which falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of benchmark datasets for NLP tasks, which falls under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of feature extraction and modulation, which is a common technique in neural networks and falls under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
